    "Researchers have investigated topics such as the use of artificially intelligent chatbots in language learning (Koç & Savaş, 2024), the use of artificial intelligence (AI) for corrective feedback (Ai, 2017), and the use of AI as language tutors (Hwang, Xie, Wah & Gašević, 2020).",
    "However, many in foreign language programs (see Perspectives column, Davin, 2024) are understandably cautious of this technology (Bekou, Ben Mhamed & Assissou, 2024; Kern, 2024; Kohnke, Moorhouse & Zou, 2023), in part due to declining enrollments (Lusin et al., 2023) and headlines regarding the replacement of foreign language departments with commercial software that uses AI (e.g.",
